ludes audio interview).</ref>  \n|-\n|[[Russell Kirk]] Paideia Prize||2012||[[Circe Institute]]||<ref>Kern, David (December 2, 2011). [https://www.circeinstitute.org/2011/12/announcing-the-2012-paideia-prize-winner-mr-wendell-berry \"Announcing the 2012 Paideia Prize Winner: Mr. Wendell Berry\"]. Circe Institute. Retrieved August 22, 2015.</ref> \n|-\n|Fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences||2013||[[American Academy of Arts and Sciences]]||<ref>[http://www.amacad.org/multimedia/pdfs/alphalist2013.pdf \"2013 Fellows and Their Affiliations at the Time of Election\"] (PDF). American Academy of Arts and Sciences. 2013. Retrieved August 22, 2015.</ref> \n|-\n|The Roosevelt Institute's Freedom Medal||2013||[[The Roosevelt Institute]]||<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.rooseveltinstitute.org/2013-four-freedoms-awards |title=The 2013 Four Freedoms Awards| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202235237/http://www.rooseveltinstitute.org/2013-four-freedoms-awards|archivedate=2013-12-02| publisher=Roosevelt Institute |accessdate=August 22, 2015}}</ref>  \n|-\n|The [[Richard C. Holbrooke]] Distinguished Achievement Award||2013||[[Dayton Literary Peace Prize]]||<ref>[http://www.bizjournals.com/dayton/news/2013/11/04/dayton-literary-peace-prize-winners.html \"Dayton Literary Peace Prize winners honored Sunday\"]. Dayton Business Journal. November 4, 2013. Retrieved August 22, 2015.</ref> \n|-\n|The [[Martin E. Marty]] Award for the Public Understanding of Religion||2013||[[American Academy of Religion]]||<ref>[https://www.aarweb.org/node/1688 \"Wendell Berry Receives Marty Award\"]. American Academy of Religion. Retrieved October 21, 2014.</ref>  \n|-\n|The [[Allen Tate]] Poetry Prize||2014||''[[The Sewanee Review]]''||<ref>[http://review.sewanee.edu/news/story/announcement-of-prizes-for-2014 \"Announcement of Prizes for 2014\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704012818/http://review.sewanee.edu/news/story/announcement-of-prizes-for-2014|date=Jul