ww.lanereport.com/118423/2019/10/wendell-berry-receives-inaugural-carl-west-literary-award/ Retrieved October 25, 2019.</ref>  \n|}\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n===Fiction===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Year !! Publisher !! Reprinted/Revised !! ISBN !! scope=\"Col\" class=\"unsortable\"|Notes\n|-\n|''Nathan Coulter''||1960||Houghton Mifflin, Boston||North Point (1985), Counterpoint (2008)||{{ISBNT|1582434093}}||Also in Three Short Novels, 2002 \nHeavily revised in 1985, including the removal of the last four chapters.\n|-\n|''A Place on Earth''||1967||Harcourt, Brace & World, New York|| Avon (1969), North Point (1983), Counterpoint (2001)||{{ISBNT|1582431248}}||Heavily revised in 1983\n|-\n|''The Memory of Old Jack''||1974||Harcourt, Brace & Jovanovich, New York||Counterpoint (1999)||{{ISBNT|1582430438}}||\n|-\n|''The Wild Birds: Six Stories of the Port William Membership''||1986||North Point, San Francisco||||{{ISBNT|0865472165}}||Also in That Distant Land: The Collected Stories, 2004\n|-\n|''Remembering''||1988||North Point, San Francisco||Counterpoint (2008)||{{ISBNT|1582434158}}||Also in Three Short Novels, 2002\n|-\n|''Fidelity: Five Stories''||1992||Pantheon, New York||||{{ISBNT|0679748318}}||Also in That Distant Land: The Collected Stories, 2004\n|-\n|''Watch With Me and Six Other Stories of the Yet-Remembered Ptolemy Proudfoot and His Wife, Miss Minnie, N\u00e9e Quinch''||1994||Pantheon, New York||||{{ISBNT|0679758542}}||Also in ''That Distant Land: The Collected Stories'', 2004\n|-\n|''A World Lost''||1996||Counterpoint, Washington, DC|||| {{ISBNT|1582434182}}||Also in Three Short Novels, 2002\n|-\n|''Jayber Crow''||2000||Counterpoint, Washington, DC||||{{ISBNT|1582431604}}||\n|-\n|''Three Short Novels (Nathan Coulter, Remembering, A World Lost)''||2002||Counterpoint, Washington, DC||||{{ISBNT|1582431787}}||\n|-\n|''Hannah Coulter''||2004||Shoemaker & Hoard, Washington, DC||Counterpoint, Berkeley (2007)||{{ISBNT|1593760361}}||In 2007 Shoemaker