United States, 1915\u20131919)\n*''[[Partisan Review]]'' (United States, 1934\u20132003)\n*''[[Pearl (literary magazine)|Pearl]]'' (United States, 1974\u20132014)\n*''[[Pen Pusher]]'' (United Kingdom, 2005\u20132011)\n*''[[Pertinent (magazine)|Pertinent]]'' (Australia, 1940\u20131947)\n*''[[The Port Folio]]'' (United States, 1800\u20131814)\n*''[[Puck (literary magazine)|Puck]]'' (United States, 1984\u20131997)\n*''[[Quarterly Review of Literature]]'' (United States, 1943\u20131999)\n*''[[The Quiet Feather]]'' (United Kingdom, 2003\u20132007)\n*''[[Ramparts (magazine)|Ramparts]]'' (United States, 1962\u20131975)\n*''[[Revue de Paris]]'' (France, 1829\u2013????)\n*''[[San Francisco Review of Books]]'' (United States, 1975\u20131997)\n*''[[The Savoy (periodical)|The Savoy]]'' (United Kingdom, 1896)\n*''[[Scribner's Magazine]]'' (United States, 1887\u20131939)\n*''[[Scripsi]]'' (Australia, 1981\u20131994)\n*''[[Shadowed Realms]]'' (online, 2004\u20132006)\n*''[[The Smart Set]]'' (United States, 1900\u20131930)\n*''[[Story (magazine)|Story]]'' (Austria and U.S., 1931\u20132000)\n*''[[Tel Quel]]'' (France, 1960\u20131982)\n*''[[The Transatlantic Review (1924)|The Transatlantic Review]]'' (France/UK, 1924)\n*''[[Transatlantic Review (1959)|Transatlantic Review]]'' (US/UK, 1959\u20131977)\n*''[[Transition (literary journal)|Transition]]'' (France, 1927\u20131938)\n*''[[Vedem]]'' (Czech Republic, 1942\u20131944)\n*''[[Wet Ink]]'' (Australia)\n*''[[Wheelhouse Magazine]]'' (2007\u20132013)\n*''[[X (magazine)|X]]'' (United Kingdom, 1959\u20131962)\n*''[[The Yale Review|Yale Review]]'' (United States, 1885\u20131892)\n*''[[The Yellow Book]]'' (United Kingdom, 1894\u20131897)\n}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Council of Literary Magazines and Presses]]\n* [[List of art magazines]]\n* [[List of political magazines]]\n* [[Science fiction magazine]]\n* [[Fantasy fiction magazine]]\n* [[Horror fiction magazine]]\n\n==References==\n*Peter Brooker and Andrew Thacker, \"The Oxford Critical and 